        "title": "Spring @Transactional serializable does not work as expected",
        "body": "<p>I use <code>Spring Data JPA<\/code> with <code>Hibernate ORM<\/code>.<\/p>\n<p>There is the common entity:<\/p>\n<pre><code>@Entity\n@Table(name = &quot;some_entity_table&quot;)\npublic class SomeEntity {\n\n   private @Id UUID uuid;\n   private String userId;\n\n   //getters and setters and constructors\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p><strong>Common Service:<\/strong><\/p>\n<pre><code>@Service\n@RequiredArgsConstructor\npublic class EntityService {\n\n  private final EntityRepository entityRepository;\n\n  @Transactional(isolation = Isolation.SERIALIZABLE, propagation = Propagation.REQUIRED)\n  public void get(String userId) {\n    1. entityRepository.findAllByUserId(userId);\n    2. SomeEntity someEntity = new SomeEntity(UUID.randomUUID(), userId);\n    3. entityRepository.save(someEntity);\n    4. List&lt;SomeEntity&gt; allByUserId = entityRepository.findAllByUserId(userId);\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>I set breakpoint in 2 line. Than I go to my database and insert row manually with the same <code>userId<\/code> and with the different <code>uuid<\/code>. I expected that hibernate before committing insert of entity, executes <code>select by userId<\/code> one more time and if count of rows changes <em>(like in my case)<\/em> exception should have been thrown. But hibernate only executes insert.<\/p>\n<p>What I doing wrong?<\/p>\n<p>P.S. <code>repeatable read<\/code> isolation works as I expected (Getting entity, changes in code, changes manually in database, save entity in code =&gt; exception thrown).<\/p>\n",
